    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, reduce the heat to low and transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling'</p><p>Squeeze juice of the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into the Thai-style coconut sauce</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the Thai-style coconut sauce and mix until the chicken is fully coated in sauce – this is your<strong> Thai-style coconut chicken</strong></p>",
